      *Rule:     TGO_TNS_USR_MNT (RTGO180)
      *Author:   A. Kress
      *Date:     November 12, 1996
      *Purpose:  Update Administration tables with User data.
      *          Requests to grant TCS access are submitted via TNS
      *          system and are fed to TCS during nightly batch
      *          processing.
      *History:
      *5/8/97 A.Kress - Had to change the substr section to match what
      *         was on the input file from TNS. Also, temporarily
      *         changed errors on TCS end to be considered complete when
      *         requests sent back to TNS
      *6/19/97 A.Kress - emergency fix. Added RQST_TP of 'ADD'.
      *6/97  A.Kress - Added substr statement for new authority level
      *         for Central File Users (CENT). Also added CENT to case
      *         statement (one for SASP,SARP) for setting up work ques.
      *         (one for SASP,SARP) for setting up work queues.
      *         Installed for Rel 2.5.  Also added bank number to org
      *         unit select.
      *8/97  A.Kress - For Rel 2.6/GL Conversion, W_KEY_CNTR_NO_C went
      *         from char(6) to char(7). TNS changed their field
      *         length for cost center from 6 to 18.
      *10/97 A.Kress - For Rel 2.6, added Private Banking authority
      *         levels as well as substr mapping to support new
      *         TNS form (#149).  New form will have a variable layout
      *         tht can be changed easily by Information Security.
      * 2/98 A.Kress - added code to assign users to non-branch org
      *         "REQUESTOR" when cost center not found on org table or
      *         when sent invalid org by TNS. Also added code to send
      *         message back to TNS when cost center is invalid. Also
      *         changed code for updates to leave user "as is" (i.e.
      *         leave auth level, wq asgnmnts intact) if cost center is
      *         is invalid, new, or a dup. EMERGENCY FIX 2/11/98
      *3/11/98 A.Kress - Changed code to assign all work queues that
      *         belong to user's org if user is Private Banking and
      *         org is not PB-DFLT. (emergency fix).
      *8/13/99 G.Dixon/John Szabo - Added code after checking the close
      *        on cursors 3 and 4 to go to batch error logger and end
      *        if there is a duplicate insert or a row not found.
      *8/13/99 sli - See changes marked 7/10.  Added code so that if
      *        the user being added or updated is a branch person and
      *        there is a not found on the call to tgaod82 which finds
      *        the org unit short name the cost center is manipulated
      *        and the tcs org unit is read again with the manipulated
      *        cost center.  In tns all branches have at least 2 cost
      *        centers, those beginning with 67 (service) and those
      *        beginning with 00 (sales).  TCS only houses one cost
      *        center per branch.  So if the cost center begins with 00
      *        and is not found the a 67 is moved to the 1st 2 digits
      *        of the cost and the sql is called again.
